      "text": "The Status of WikiWords. WikiWords as topics go away. The WikiWord gave us a quick way of creating a linked page, a quickness that the wiki was named for. With FedWiki things slow down. The page can be more formally titled. It needs to be. WikiWords are passé anyway. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "53c53448a753f450",
      "text": "One level of headings. Flattening the page. Ward et al are suggesting one level - h3 - in a page, the title being h1. This serves to prompt creating a topic and developing in its own page rather than creating a nested list. This takes us back to Freestanding Pages. We can force a second level with run-in bolds for headings."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9c8f3381e63e7adf",
      "text": "Reduced formatting such as bullet lists. \"In federated wiki we try to use a minimum of formatting.\" Bullets have become a way of avoiding exposition and might be better served by run-in heads or paragraphs. Bold gives us a way of creating a run-in heading, and we need italics to mark references, etc."
    },
