      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1e6023aba29e5e06",
      "text": "Emphasis on focused pages that can stand alone but don't need to. FedWikis pages are more molecular that traditional wiki pages. We're keeping in mind how paragraph-level content in a FedWiki federation will be picked up and reused."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "6562aabd962f2baf",
      "text": "The paragraph as a unit of composition. To add content, you add a paragraph using the Factory. The paragraph is draggable, within the page or across pages. The freedom of movement is an affordance that makes revision, re-mixing, repurposing, and refactoring central to composing. [[Molecular Paragraphs]] Paragraphs \"are free to roam,\" writes Ward, and that has implications for linking."
    },
